{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01PvDZPHctFPWMwq3ixuXodm","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Specification: 001 Coinflip\n     2→\n     3→## Meta\n     4→\n     5→| Field | Value |\n     6→|-------|-------|\n     7→| Status | Ready |\n     8→| Ideation | Complete |\n     9→| Priority | P0 |\n    10→| Phase | 1 |\n    11→| NR_OF_TRIES | 7 |\n    12→\n    13→---\n    14→\n    15→## Overview\n    16→\n    17→Coinflip is the simplest game on the platform and the first end-to-end delivery target. Two players wager equal amounts in a 1v1 match. A verifiable random function determines one winner who takes the entire pot minus the platform fee. It validates the full wager-to-settlement flow before Crash development begins.\n    18→\n    19→## User Stories\n    20→\n    21→- As a player, I want to create a coinflip match by choosing a tier and side so that I can challenge an opponent at stakes I'm comfortable with.\n    22→- As a player, I want to browse open coinflip lobbies so that I can join a match quickly.\n    23→- As a player, I want to see a fair coin flip animation and result so that I trust the outcome is legitimate.\n    24→- As a winner, I want my payout settled on-chain so that I can claim my winnings trustlessly.\n    25→- As a player, I want to verify the fairness of any completed match so that I can confirm the result was not manipulated.\n    26→\n    27→---\n    28→\n    29→## Scope Alignment\n    30→\n    31→- **`docs/SCOPE.md` references**: Section 2 (Product Scope - V1 In Scope: Coinflip), Section 5 (V1 Game Scope - Coinflip), Section 8 (Delivery Plan - Phase 1)\n    32→- **Scope status**: V1 In Scope\n    33→- **Phase boundary**: Phase 1 - Coinflip End-to-End\n    34→\n    35→## Required Context Files\n    36→\n    37→- `sources/rng-utopia/docs/COINFLIP.md` (game concept source)\n    38→- `sources/rng-utopia/docs/PLATFORM.md` (tier-based betting, platform fee, provably fair system)\n    39→- `docs/SCOPE.md` (scope boundary and shared game requirements)\n    40→\n    41→## Contract Files\n    42→\n    43→### Frontend (Existing UI — preserve design/UX)\n    44→- `apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/context/CoinflipContext.tsx` — game state management\n    45→- `apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/components/` — ActiveMatchView, CoinAnimation, CoinSideSelector, MatchCard, OpenMatchesList\n    46→- `apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/types.ts` — frontend type definitions\n    47→- `apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/utils/mock-simulation.ts` — mock to be replaced with real chain calls\n    48→\n    49→### Game Engine (TS instruction builders)\n    50→- `packages/game-engine/src/coinflip.ts` — PDA derivation, instruction builders, payout calc\n    51→- `packages/game-engine/src/types.ts` — shared types + fee constants\n    52→- `packages/game-engine/src/payouts.ts` — payout math\n    53→\n    54→### On-Chain (Anchor programs — current implementation)\n    55→- `solana/programs/coinflip/` — Coinflip program (MagicBlock Ephemeral VRF)\n    56→- `solana/programs/platform/` — Platform program (player profiles, fee config)\n    57→- `solana/shared/` — Shared Rust lib (fees, tiers, constants)\n    58→\n    59→---\n    60→\n    61→## Functional Requirements\n    62→\n    63→### FR-1: Match Creation\n    64→\n    65→A player can create a new coinflip match by selecting a betting tier (Iron through Diamond) and a side (Heads or Tails). The match appears in the open games list for other players to join.\n    66→\n    67→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n    68→- [ ] Player can select one of six tiers (Iron 0.005, Bronze 0.01, Silver 0.1, Gold 0.25, Platinum 0.5, Diamond 1 SOL)\n    69→- [ ] Player can choose Heads or Tails\n    70→- [ ] Created match appears in the lobby browser with creator name, tier, wager amount, and side chosen\n    71→- [ ] Match creation requires a connected wallet with sufficient balance\n    72→- [ ] Only one active match per player at a time (enforced on-chain via PDA constraint)\n    73→\n    74→### FR-2: Match Joining\n    75→\n    76→A second player can join an open match. The joiner is automatically assigned the opposite side. Both players must wager the same tier amount.\n    77→\n    78→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n    79→- [ ] Player can browse open matches filtered by tier and sorted by newest/oldest\n    80→- [ ] Joining assigns the opposite side automatically\n    81→- [ ] Both players' wagers are equal (tier-enforced)\n    82→- [ ] Tier selection is locked once the bet is placed\n    83→- [ ] Join requires connected wallet with sufficient balance\n    84→\n    85→### FR-3: Flip Resolution\n    86→\n    87→Once both players have joined, a coin flip occurs using VRF. The flip animation plays for approximately 3 seconds, then the result is revealed.\n    88→\n    89→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n    90→- [ ] Flip begins immediately when both players are committed\n    91→- [ ] VRF determines the outcome (Heads or Tails)\n    92→- [ ] Result is deterministic and reproducible from the VRF seed\n    93→- [ ] Flip animation plays with coin rotation and landing\n    94→\n    95→### FR-4: Settlement and Payout\n    96→\n    97→The winner receives the total pool minus the platform fee. Settlement is recorded on-chain.\n    98→\n    99→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   100→- [ ] Winner payout = total_pool x 0.97 (3% platform fee)\n   101→- [ ] Platform fee is collected to treasury PDA\n   102→- [ ] Payout eligibility is recorded on-chain\n   103→- [ ] Winner can claim funds successfully\n   104→- [ ] Settlement is idempotent (cannot double-settle)\n   105→- [ ] Replay protection for signed actions\n   106→\n   107→### FR-5: Fairness Verification\n   108→\n   109→Players can verify the outcome of any completed match by inspecting the VRF inputs and recalculating the result.\n   110→\n   111→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   112→- [ ] Completed match displays VRF seed/proof details\n   113→- [ ] Players can independently verify the result matches the VRF output\n   114→- [ ] Verification is accessible from match history and result screen\n   115→\n   116→### FR-6: Lobby Browser UI\n   117→\n   118→A browsable list of open coinflip matches with filtering and creation controls.\n   119→\n   120→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   121→- [ ] Open games list shows creator name/avatar, tier, wager amount, side, and join button\n   122→- [ ] Filter by tier\n   123→- [ ] Sort by newest/oldest/amount\n   124→- [ ] Create Game panel with tier selection grid and Heads/Tails toggle\n   125→- [ ] Estimated wait time shown (derived from recent match fill rate — deferred to post-MVP polish if data unavailable)\n   126→\n   127→### FR-7: Active Game and Result UI\n   128→\n   129→The in-match view showing both players, coin flip animation, and result.\n   130→\n   131→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   132→- [ ] Both players shown with avatars, names, and wager amounts\n   133→- [ ] 3D coin flip animation with multiple rotations and gradual slowdown\n   134→- [ ] Winning side highlighted with glow effect\n   135→- [ ] \"YOU WIN!\" or \"YOU LOSE\" overlay displayed\n   136→- [ ] Payout amount shown for winner\n   137→- [ ] Quick rematch option available after result\n   138→\n   139→### FR-8: Audio Feedback\n   140→\n   141→Sound effects accompany the coinflip experience.\n   142→\n   143→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n   144→- [ ] Coin flip spinning sound during animation\n   145→- [ ] Dramatic pause before landing\n   146→- [ ] Victory sound for winner\n   147→- [ ] Coin clink on landing\n   148→\n   149→---\n   150→\n   151→## Success Criteria\n   152→\n   153→- A player can create a match, have it joined, see the flip, and receive payout in a single uninterrupted flow\n   154→- Settlement correctness: winner always receives exactly (pool x 0.97), fee always reaches treasury\n   155→- Any completed match can be independently verified for fairness\n   156→- Match creation to resolution completes within 10 seconds of both players joining\n   157→- Error states (insufficient balance, network failure, wallet disconnect) are clearly communicated\n   158→\n   159→---\n   160→\n   161→## Dependencies\n   162→\n   163→- Wallet connection via `@solana/wallet-adapter-react` (Privy removed)\n   164→- Coinflip Anchor program (`solana/programs/coinflip`) with MagicBlock Ephemeral VRF\n   165→- Platform Anchor program (`solana/programs/platform`) for player profiles + fee config\n   166→- `packages/anchor-client/` (generated from IDL via `scripts/sync-idl`)\n   167→- Shared UI components (`packages/ui/`) for buttons, modals, cards, toasts\n   168→- Dev environment: Anchor CLI 0.32.1, Solana CLI 2.3.13, Rust toolchain\n   169→\n   170→## Assumptions\n   171→\n   172→- Tier amounts are fixed at the values defined in PLATFORM.md\n   173→- Platform fee is 3% (300 bps). Confirmed in `docs/FOUNDATIONS.md` §8. Split: 200 bps revenue, 50 bps cashback, 50 bps rewards.\n   174→- VRF provider: MagicBlock Ephemeral VRF. Confirmed in `docs/FOUNDATIONS.md` §5.\n   175→- Non-custodial wallet flow via `@solana/wallet-adapter-react` (no Privy, no internal balance model)\n   176→- Existing on-chain programs are legacy — coinflip program will be rewritten from scratch (VRF integration pattern preserved)\n   177→\n   178→---\n   179→\n   180→## Validation Plan\n   181→\n   182→| # | Acceptance Criterion | Validation Method | Evidence Required |\n   183→|---|---------------------|-------------------|-------------------|\n   184→| 1 | Match creation with tier + side | Create match via UI, verify lobby listing | Screenshot of lobby with new match |\n   185→| 2 | Match joining assigns opposite side | Join match, verify side assignment | Screenshot showing both players |\n   186→| 3 | VRF determines outcome | Inspect VRF output, verify determinism | VRF proof + recalculated result |\n   187→| 4 | Winner payout = pool x 0.97 | Check on-chain settlement transaction | Explorer link showing amounts |\n   188→| 5 | Platform fee reaches treasury | Check treasury PDA balance | Explorer link showing fee transfer |\n   189→| 6 | Settlement is idempotent | Attempt double-settle, verify rejection | Error response or no-op proof |\n   190→| 7 | Fairness verification works | Use verification UI to recalculate result | Screenshot of verification view |\n   191→| 8 | End-to-end flow completes | Full playthrough from create to claim | Video or step-by-step screenshots |\n   192→\n   193→---\n   194→\n   195→## Completion Signal\n   196→\n   197→### Implementation Checklist\n   198→\n   199→**On-chain Foundation**\n   200→- [x] [on-chain] CoinflipConfig PDA + initialize_config instruction (done: TDD stubs commit)\n   201→- [x] [on-chain] CoinflipMatch state + create_match instruction with tier validation + escrow (done: TDD stubs commit)\n   202→- [x] [on-chain] Align shared crate tiers with spec: 6 tiers Iron(0.005)→Bronze(0.01)→Silver(0.1)→Gold(0.25)→Platinum(0.5)→Diamond(1.0 SOL). Update `solana/shared/src/tiers.rs` amounts to `[5_000_000, 10_000_000, 100_000_000, 250_000_000, 500_000_000, 1_000_000_000]`, update tier name comments to Iron/Bronze/Silver/Gold/Platinum/Diamond. Update test constant `TIER_IRON_AMOUNT` to `5_000_000` in `solana/tests/coinflip.ts`. Verify: `anchor build` succeeds + 5 existing passing tests still pass. (done: iteration 1)\n   203→\n   204→**Coinflip Instructions**\n   205→- [x] [on-chain] Implement join_match — check `phase==WAITING` (InvalidPhase), reject `opponent==creator` (CannotJoinOwnMatch), transfer `entry_amount` from opponent to match PDA via system program CPI, set `opponent` field + `phase=LOCKED`. Verify: 3 join_match bankrun tests pass. (done: iteration 2)\n   206→- [x] [on-chain] Implement resolve_match — check `phase==LOCKED` (InvalidPhase), check `signer==config.oracle_authority` (UnauthorizedOracle), compute `result = shared::constants::from_randomness(randomness[0])`, set winner (creator if `result==creator_side`, else opponent), set `result` + `phase=SETTLED`. Verify: 5 resolve_match bankrun tests pass. (done: iteration 3)\n   207→- [x] [on-chain] Implement claim_payout — check `phase==SETTLED` (InvalidPhase), check `signer==match.winner` (NotWinner), check `!match.claimed` (AlreadyClaimed), compute `fee = shared::fees::calculate_fee(pool)` where `pool = entry_amount * 2`, transfer `(pool - fee)` to winner + `fee` to treasury via system program CPI, set `claimed=true`, close match account (rent refund → creator). Verify: 5 claim_payout bankrun tests pass. (done: iteration 4)\n   208→- [x] [on-chain] Implement cancel_match — check `phase==WAITING` (CannotCancel), creator enforced by PDA seeds, refund full escrow (entry_amount + rent) to creator, close match account. Verify: 3 cancel_match + 2 full lifecycle bankrun tests pass. **All 23 tests green.** (done: iteration 5)\n   209→\n   210→**Platform Program**\n   211→- [x] [on-chain] Create platform program scaffold: PlatformConfig PDA (seeds: `[b\"platform_config\"]`, fields: authority, treasury, `fee_bps=300`, bump) + `initialize_platform` instruction. PlayerProfile PDA (seeds: `[b\"player_profile\", wallet]`, fields: authority, total_games, wins, total_wagered, total_won, bump) + `create_player_profile` instruction. Add to `Anchor.toml` and workspace `Cargo.toml`. Write bankrun tests for config init + profile creation. Verify: `anchor build` succeeds + platform tests pass. (done: iteration 6)\n   212→- [x] [on-chain] Add CPI from coinflip `claim_payout` → platform `update_player_profile`: increment both players' `total_games`, winner's `wins`, update `total_wagered`/`total_won` amounts. Add platform program to coinflip test context (deploy + init config + create profiles in setup). Verify: updated coinflip bankrun tests pass with CPI calls. (done: iteration 7)\n   213→\n   214→**Game Engine Alignment**\n   215→- [x] [engine] Create anchor-client package: `anchor build` → generate IDL, create `packages/anchor-client/` with typed exports for coinflip + platform programs, add `scripts/sync-idl` script that copies `target/idl/*.json` + `target/types/*.ts` into the package. Verify: package builds, types are importable, `pnpm lint` passes. (done: iteration 1)\n   216→- [x] [engine] Align game-engine with on-chain: update `types.ts` (`COIN_SIDE_VALUES`: heads=0/tails=1; `COINFLIP_PHASE_VALUES`: created=0/ready=1/flipping=2/complete=3; tiers match spec). Rewrite `coinflip.ts` PDA derivation — delete BOLT ECS pool/entry/state PDAs, add `getMatchPda(creator)` + `getConfigPda()` matching on-chain seeds, update `PROGRAM_IDS` to real coinflip program ID. Verify: `pnpm lint` + `pnpm typecheck` pass in game-engine package. (done: iteration 7)\n   217→\n   218→**Frontend Wiring**\n   219→- [ ] [frontend] Wire CoinflipContext to anchor-client: replace mock state management with on-chain program queries. Delete `mock-simulation.ts`. Wire `createMatch`/`joinMatch`/`cancelMatch`/`claimPayout` to real on-chain instructions via wallet-adapter. Verify: `pnpm lint` + `pnpm typecheck` pass in platform app.\n   220→- [ ] [frontend] Wire lobby browser: read open matches via `getProgramAccounts` with coinflip match account filter, implement tier filter + sort. Add error handling for insufficient balance, wallet disconnect, and transaction failure. Verify: `pnpm build` succeeds for platform app.\n   221→\n   222→### Scope Decisions\n   223→\n   224→- **Tiers**: Spec/frontend values canonical (Iron→Diamond, 0.005→1.0 SOL). On-chain shared crate updated to match.\n   225→- **Side discriminants**: 0/1 canonical (heads=0, tails=1). Game-engine updated to match on-chain.\n   226→- **VRF**: Mock oracle authority (test keypair signs resolve_match). MagicBlock Ephemeral VRF deferred.\n   227→- **Platform program**: Included with CPI for player profile updates on settlement.\n   228→- **Deferred to later spec**: Audio integration, fairness verification UI, active game animation polish, Playwright integration tests, devnet deployment.\n   229→\n   230→### Iteration Instructions\n   231→\n   232→Each checklist item is one autonomous iteration (`claude -p` invocation). The agent:\n   233→1. Reads this spec + history.md for prior context\n   234→2. Implements the next unchecked item\n   235→3. Runs the verification command specified in the item\n   236→4. If verification passes → checks the box, commits, outputs `<promise>DONE</promise>`\n   237→5. If verification fails → outputs `<blocker>description</blocker>` and exits\n   238→\n   239→**Only when ALL items are checked, output:** `<promise>DONE</promise>`\n   240→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"eb85923b-8763-4260-a88f-751dbcd29bcb","uuid":"5f6d0b74-2313-4cbb-a49b-cbeb17a0a298","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/docs/specs/001-coinflip/spec.md","content":"# Specification: 001 Coinflip\n\n## Meta\n\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| Status | Ready |\n| Ideation | Complete |\n| Priority | P0 |\n| Phase | 1 |\n| NR_OF_TRIES | 7 |\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nCoinflip is the simplest game on the platform and the first end-to-end delivery target. Two players wager equal amounts in a 1v1 match. A verifiable random function determines one winner who takes the entire pot minus the platform fee. It validates the full wager-to-settlement flow before Crash development begins.\n\n## User Stories\n\n- As a player, I want to create a coinflip match by choosing a tier and side so that I can challenge an opponent at stakes I'm comfortable with.\n- As a player, I want to browse open coinflip lobbies so that I can join a match quickly.\n- As a player, I want to see a fair coin flip animation and result so that I trust the outcome is legitimate.\n- As a winner, I want my payout settled on-chain so that I can claim my winnings trustlessly.\n- As a player, I want to verify the fairness of any completed match so that I can confirm the result was not manipulated.\n\n---\n\n## Scope Alignment\n\n- **`docs/SCOPE.md` references**: Section 2 (Product Scope - V1 In Scope: Coinflip), Section 5 (V1 Game Scope - Coinflip), Section 8 (Delivery Plan - Phase 1)\n- **Scope status**: V1 In Scope\n- **Phase boundary**: Phase 1 - Coinflip End-to-End\n\n## Required Context Files\n\n- `sources/rng-utopia/docs/COINFLIP.md` (game concept source)\n- `sources/rng-utopia/docs/PLATFORM.md` (tier-based betting, platform fee, provably fair system)\n- `docs/SCOPE.md` (scope boundary and shared game requirements)\n\n## Contract Files\n\n### Frontend (Existing UI — preserve design/UX)\n- `apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/context/CoinflipContext.tsx` — game state management\n- `apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/components/` — ActiveMatchView, CoinAnimation, CoinSideSelector, MatchCard, OpenMatchesList\n- `apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/types.ts` — frontend type definitions\n- `apps/platform/src/features/coinflip/utils/mock-simulation.ts` — mock to be replaced with real chain calls\n\n### Game Engine (TS instruction builders)\n- `packages/game-engine/src/coinflip.ts` — PDA derivation, instruction builders, payout calc\n- `packages/game-engine/src/types.ts` — shared types + fee constants\n- `packages/game-engine/src/payouts.ts` — payout math\n\n### On-Chain (Anchor programs — current implementation)\n- `solana/programs/coinflip/` — Coinflip program (MagicBlock Ephemeral VRF)\n- `solana/programs/platform/` — Platform program (player profiles, fee config)\n- `solana/shared/` — Shared Rust lib (fees, tiers, constants)\n\n---\n\n## Functional Requirements\n\n### FR-1: Match Creation\n\nA player can create a new coinflip match by selecting a betting tier (Iron through Diamond) and a side (Heads or Tails). The match appears in the open games list for other players to join.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Player can select one of six tiers (Iron 0.005, Bronze 0.01, Silver 0.1, Gold 0.25, Platinum 0.5, Diamond 1 SOL)\n- [ ] Player can choose Heads or Tails\n- [ ] Created match appears in the lobby browser with creator name, tier, wager amount, and side chosen\n- [ ] Match creation requires a connected wallet with sufficient balance\n- [ ] Only one active match per player at a time (enforced on-chain via PDA constraint)\n\n### FR-2: Match Joining\n\nA second player can join an open match. The joiner is automatically assigned the opposite side. Both players must wager the same tier amount.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Player can browse open matches filtered by tier and sorted by newest/oldest\n- [ ] Joining assigns the opposite side automatically\n- [ ] Both players' wagers are equal (tier-enforced)\n- [ ] Tier selection is locked once the bet is placed\n- [ ] Join requires connected wallet with sufficient balance\n\n### FR-3: Flip Resolution\n\nOnce both players have joined, a coin flip occurs using VRF. The flip animation plays for approximately 3 seconds, then the result is revealed.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Flip begins immediately when both players are committed\n- [ ] VRF determines the outcome (Heads or Tails)\n- [ ] Result is deterministic and reproducible from the VRF seed\n- [ ] Flip animation plays with coin rotation and landing\n\n### FR-4: Settlement and Payout\n\nThe winner receives the total pool minus the platform fee. Settlement is recorded on-chain.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Winner payout = total_pool x 0.97 (3% platform fee)\n- [ ] Platform fee is collected to treasury PDA\n- [ ] Payout eligibility is recorded on-chain\n- [ ] Winner can claim funds successfully\n- [ ] Settlement is idempotent (cannot double-settle)\n- [ ] Replay protection for signed actions\n\n### FR-5: Fairness Verification\n\nPlayers can verify the outcome of any completed match by inspecting the VRF inputs and recalculating the result.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Completed match displays VRF seed/proof details\n- [ ] Players can independently verify the result matches the VRF output\n- [ ] Verification is accessible from match history and result screen\n\n### FR-6: Lobby Browser UI\n\nA browsable list of open coinflip matches with filtering and creation controls.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Open games list shows creator name/avatar, tier, wager amount, side, and join button\n- [ ] Filter by tier\n- [ ] Sort by newest/oldest/amount\n- [ ] Create Game panel with tier selection grid and Heads/Tails toggle\n- [ ] Estimated wait time shown (derived from recent match fill rate — deferred to post-MVP polish if data unavailable)\n\n### FR-7: Active Game and Result UI\n\nThe in-match view showing both players, coin flip animation, and result.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Both players shown with avatars, names, and wager amounts\n- [ ] 3D coin flip animation with multiple rotations and gradual slowdown\n- [ ] Winning side highlighted with glow effect\n- [ ] \"YOU WIN!\" or \"YOU LOSE\" overlay displayed\n- [ ] Payout amount shown for winner\n- [ ] Quick rematch option available after result\n\n### FR-8: Audio Feedback\n\nSound effects accompany the coinflip experience.\n\n**Acceptance Criteria:**\n- [ ] Coin flip spinning sound during animation\n- [ ] Dramatic pause before landing\n- [ ] Victory sound for winner\n- [ ] Coin clink on landing\n\n---\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n- A player can create a match, have it joined, see the flip, and receive payout in a single uninterrupted flow\n- Settlement correctness: winner always receives exactly (pool x 0.97), fee always reaches treasury\n- Any completed match can be independently verified for fairness\n- Match creation to resolution completes within 10 seconds of both players joining\n- Error states (insufficient balance, network failure, wallet disconnect) are clearly communicated\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n- Wallet connection via `@solana/wallet-adapter-react` (Privy removed)\n- Coinflip Anchor program (`solana/programs/coinflip`) with MagicBlock Ephemeral VRF\n- Platform Anchor program (`solana/programs/platform`) for player profiles + fee config\n- `packages/anchor-client/` (generated from IDL via `scripts/sync-idl`)\n- Shared UI components (`packages/ui/`) for buttons, modals, cards, toasts\n- Dev environment: Anchor CLI 0.32.1, Solana CLI 2.3.13, Rust toolchain\n\n## Assumptions\n\n- Tier amounts are fixed at the values defined in PLATFORM.md\n- Platform fee is 3% (300 bps). Confirmed in `docs/FOUNDATIONS.md` §8. Split: 200 bps revenue, 50 bps cashback, 50 bps rewards.\n- VRF provider: MagicBlock Ephemeral VRF. Confirmed in `docs/FOUNDATIONS.md` §5.\n- Non-custodial wallet flow via `@solana/wallet-adapter-react` (no Privy, no internal balance model)\n- Existing on-chain programs are legacy — coinflip program will be rewritten from scratch (VRF integration pattern preserved)\n\n---\n\n## Validation Plan\n\n| # | Acceptance Criterion | Validation Method | Evidence Required |\n|---|---------------------|-------------------|-------------------|\n| 1 | Match creation with tier + side | Create match via UI, verify lobby listing | Screenshot of lobby with new match |\n| 2 | Match joining assigns opposite side | Join match, verify side assignment | Screenshot showing both players |\n| 3 | VRF determines outcome | Inspect VRF output, verify determinism | VRF proof + recalculated result |\n| 4 | Winner payout = pool x 0.97 | Check on-chain settlement transaction | Explorer link showing amounts |\n| 5 | Platform fee reaches treasury | Check treasury PDA balance | Explorer link showing fee transfer |\n| 6 | Settlement is idempotent | Attempt double-settle, verify rejection | Error response or no-op proof |\n| 7 | Fairness verification works | Use verification UI to recalculate result | Screenshot of verification view |\n| 8 | End-to-end flow completes | Full playthrough from create to claim | Video or step-by-step screenshots |\n\n---\n\n## Completion Signal\n\n### Implementation Checklist\n\n**On-chain Foundation**\n- [x] [on-chain] CoinflipConfig PDA + initialize_config instruction (done: TDD stubs commit)\n- [x] [on-chain] CoinflipMatch state + create_match instruction with tier validation + escrow (done: TDD stubs commit)\n- [x] [on-chain] Align shared crate tiers with spec: 6 tiers Iron(0.005)→Bronze(0.01)→Silver(0.1)→Gold(0.25)→Platinum(0.5)→Diamond(1.0 SOL). Update `solana/shared/src/tiers.rs` amounts to `[5_000_000, 10_000_000, 100_000_000, 250_000_000, 500_000_000, 1_000_000_000]`, update tier name comments to Iron/Bronze/Silver/Gold/Platinum/Diamond. Update test constant `TIER_IRON_AMOUNT` to `5_000_000` in `solana/tests/coinflip.ts`. Verify: `anchor build` succeeds + 5 existing passing tests still pass. (done: iteration 1)\n\n**Coinflip Instructions**\n- [x] [on-chain] Implement join_match — check `phase==WAITING` (InvalidPhase), reject `opponent==creator` (CannotJoinOwnMatch), transfer `entry_amount` from opponent to match PDA via system program CPI, set `opponent` field + `phase=LOCKED`. Verify: 3 join_match bankrun tests pass. (done: iteration 2)\n- [x] [on-chain] Implement resolve_match — check `phase==LOCKED` (InvalidPhase), check `signer==config.oracle_authority` (UnauthorizedOracle), compute `result = shared::constants::from_randomness(randomness[0])`, set winner (creator if `result==creator_side`, else opponent), set `result` + `phase=SETTLED`. Verify: 5 resolve_match bankrun tests pass. (done: iteration 3)\n- [x] [on-chain] Implement claim_payout — check `phase==SETTLED` (InvalidPhase), check `signer==match.winner` (NotWinner), check `!match.claimed` (AlreadyClaimed), compute `fee = shared::fees::calculate_fee(pool)` where `pool = entry_amount * 2`, transfer `(pool - fee)` to winner + `fee` to treasury via system program CPI, set `claimed=true`, close match account (rent refund → creator). Verify: 5 claim_payout bankrun tests pass. (done: iteration 4)\n- [x] [on-chain] Implement cancel_match — check `phase==WAITING` (CannotCancel), creator enforced by PDA seeds, refund full escrow (entry_amount + rent) to creator, close match account. Verify: 3 cancel_match + 2 full lifecycle bankrun tests pass. **All 23 tests green.** (done: iteration 5)\n\n**Platform Program**\n- [x] [on-chain] Create platform program scaffold: PlatformConfig PDA (seeds: `[b\"platform_config\"]`, fields: authority, treasury, `fee_bps=300`, bump) + `initialize_platform` instruction. PlayerProfile PDA (seeds: `[b\"player_profile\", wallet]`, fields: authority, total_games, wins, total_wagered, total_won, bump) + `create_player_profile` instruction. Add to `Anchor.toml` and workspace `Cargo.toml`. Write bankrun tests for config init + profile creation. Verify: `anchor build` succeeds + platform tests pass. (done: iteration 6)\n- [x] [on-chain] Add CPI from coinflip `claim_payout` → platform `update_player_profile`: increment both players' `total_games`, winner's `wins`, update `total_wagered`/`total_won` amounts. Add platform program to coinflip test context (deploy + init config + create profiles in setup). Verify: updated coinflip bankrun tests pass with CPI calls. (done: iteration 7)\n\n**Game Engine Alignment**\n- [x] [engine] Create anchor-client package: `anchor build` → generate IDL, create `packages/anchor-client/` with typed exports for coinflip + platform programs, add `scripts/sync-idl` script that copies `target/idl/*.json` + `target/types/*.ts` into the package. Verify: package builds, types are importable, `pnpm lint` passes. (done: iteration 1)\n- [x] [engine] Align game-engine with on-chain: update `types.ts` (`COIN_SIDE_VALUES`: heads=0/tails=1; `COINFLIP_PHASE_VALUES`: created=0/ready=1/flipping=2/complete=3; tiers match spec). Rewrite `coinflip.ts` PDA derivation — delete BOLT ECS pool/entry/state PDAs, add `getMatchPda(creator)` + `getConfigPda()` matching on-chain seeds, update `PROGRAM_IDS` to real coinflip program ID. Verify: `pnpm lint` + `pnpm typecheck` pass in game-engine package. (done: iteration 7)\n\n**Frontend Wiring**\n- [ ] [frontend] Wire CoinflipContext to anchor-client: replace mock state management with on-chain program queries. Delete `mock-simulation.ts`. Wire `createMatch`/`joinMatch`/`cancelMatch`/`claimPayout` to real on-chain instructions via wallet-adapter. Verify: `pnpm lint` + `pnpm typecheck` pass in platform app.\n- [ ] [frontend] Wire lobby browser: read open matches via `getProgramAccounts` with coinflip match account filter, implement tier filter + sort. Add error handling for insufficient balance, wallet disconnect, and transaction failure. Verify: `pnpm build` succeeds for platform app.\n\n### Scope Decisions\n\n- **Tiers**: Spec/frontend values canonical (Iron→Diamond, 0.005→1.0 SOL). On-chain shared crate updated to match.\n- **Side discriminants**: 0/1 canonical (heads=0, tails=1). Game-engine updated to match on-chain.\n- **VRF**: Mock oracle authority (test keypair signs resolve_match). MagicBlock Ephemeral VRF deferred.\n- **Platform program**: Included with CPI for player profile updates on settlement.\n- **Deferred to later spec**: Audio integration, fairness verification UI, active game animation polish, Playwright integration tests, devnet deployment.\n\n### Iteration Instructions\n\nEach checklist item is one autonomous iteration (`claude -p` invocation). The agent:\n1. Reads this spec + history.md for prior context\n2. Implements the next unchecked item\n3. Runs the verification command specified in the item\n4. If verification passes → checks the box, commits, outputs `<promise>DONE</promise>`\n5. If verification fails → outputs `<blocker>description</blocker>` and exits\n\n**Only when ALL items are checked, output:** `<promise>DONE</promise>`\n","numLines":240,"startLine":1,"totalLines":240}}}
