{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01YCTQuKBLEy2YtcyQ9ZrCui","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have all the information. Let me compile a comprehensive report:\n\n## Codebase Analysis Report\n\n### 1. Wallet Adapter Setup\n\n**Location**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/wallet/`\n\n**`@rng-utopia/wallet/hooks` Exports**:\n\nThe package exports a lightweight `useWallet` hook:\n\n```typescript\n// File: packages/wallet/src/hooks.ts\nexport { useWallet } from \"./useWallet\";\nexport { useBalance } from \"./useBalance\";\nexport type { BalanceResult } from \"./useBalance\";\nexport type { WalletState, WalletContextValue } from \"./types\";\n```\n\n**`useWallet` Hook Implementation**:\n\n```typescript\n// File: packages/wallet/src/useWallet.ts\nimport { useContext } from \"react\";\nimport { WalletContext } from \"./context\";\nimport { WalletContextValue } from \"./types\";\n\nexport function useWallet(): WalletContextValue {\n  const context = useContext(WalletContext);\n  if (!context) {\n    throw new Error(\"useWallet must be used within a WalletProvider\");\n  }\n  return context;\n}\n```\n\n**`WalletContextValue` Type Shape**:\n\n```typescript\n// File: packages/wallet/src/types.ts\nexport interface WalletContextValue extends WalletState {\n  connect: () => Promise<void>;\n  disconnect: () => Promise<void>;\n  sendTransaction: (transaction: Transaction) => Promise<string>;\n  signMessage: (message: Uint8Array) => Promise<Uint8Array>;\n  isMock?: boolean;\n  getBalance?: () => number;\n  getBalanceLamports?: () => number;\n  updateBalance?: (deltaLamports: number) => void;\n}\n\nexport interface WalletState {\n  connected: boolean;\n  connecting: boolean;\n  address: string | null;\n  publicKey: PublicKey | null;\n}\n```\n\n**Current Provider Setup** (main.tsx):\n\n```typescript\n// File: apps/platform/src/main.tsx\nimport { MockWalletProvider } from \"@rng-utopia/wallet/mock\";\n\ncreateRoot(rootElement).render(\n  <StrictMode>\n    <ErrorBoundary>\n      <MockWalletProvider>\n        <App />\n      </MockWalletProvider>\n    </ErrorBoundary>\n  </StrictMode>\n);\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. Anchor-Client Package Exports\n\n**Location**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/anchor-client/src/index.ts`\n\n**Main Exports**:\n\n```typescript\n// IDL JSON (runtime values)\nimport CoinflipIDL from \"./coinflip.json\" with { type: \"json\" };\nimport PlatformIDL from \"./platform.json\" with { type: \"json\" };\n\n// Type-safe IDL types (compile-time)\nexport type { Coinflip } from \"./coinflip.js\";\nexport type { Platform } from \"./platform.js\";\n\n// Re-export IDLs as typed constants\nexport { CoinflipIDL, PlatformIDL };\n```\n\nThe package exports:\n- **`Coinflip`** - TypeScript type for Coinflip program IDL\n- **`Platform`** - TypeScript type for Platform program IDL\n- **`CoinflipIDL`** - Runtime JSON constant\n- **`PlatformIDL`** - Runtime JSON constant\n\n---\n\n### 3. Coinflip IDL Type Shape\n\n**File**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/packages/anchor-client/src/coinflip.ts`\n\n**Top-level Type Structure**:\n\n```typescript\nexport type Coinflip = {\n  \"address\": \"H8Q2R1bUxzfUkV6WRRiZxYWwGfCr794AcnskWpsRQJf3\",\n  \"metadata\": {\n    \"name\": \"coinflip\",\n    \"version\": \"0.1.0\",\n    \"spec\": \"0.1.0\"\n  },\n  \"instructions\": [\n    // 5 instructions: cancelMatch, claimPayout, createMatch, initializeConfig, joinMatch, resolveMatch\n  ],\n  \"accounts\": [\n    // 2 accounts: coinflipConfig, coinflipMatch\n  ],\n  \"errors\": [\n    // 8 error codes (6100-6108)\n  ],\n  \"types\": [\n    // 2 types: coinflipConfig, coinflipMatch\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n**Key Account Types**:\n\n```typescript\n// coinflipConfig (PDA seeds: [b\"coinflip_config\"])\n{\n  authority: pubkey\n  oracleAuthority: pubkey\n  treasury: pubkey\n  bump: u8\n}\n\n// coinflipMatch (PDA seeds: [b\"match\", creator.key().as_ref()])\n