{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01Ajg5Gm6UuaWbkCwxsMSyim","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have a clear picture. Let me plan the changes for this checklist item:\n\n**Checklist item**: `[frontend] Wire CoinflipContext to anchor-client: replace mock state management with on-chain program queries. Delete mock-simulation.ts. Wire createMatch/joinMatch/cancelMatch/claimPayout to real on-chain instructions via wallet-adapter. Verify: pnpm lint + pnpm typecheck pass in platform app.`\n\nKey observations:\n1. `mock-simulation.ts` is imported by **many** other features (boss-raid, player-profile, quests, lord-of-rngs, etc.) — not just coinflip. The spec says \"Delete `mock-simulation.ts`\" but that refers to the *coinflip* mock. Other features have their own mock files.\n2. `truncateAddress` from the coinflip mock is re-exported from `coinflip/index.ts` and used by other features.\n3. `ActiveMatchView.tsx` imports `getOppositeSide` from the mock.\n4. The wallet provider is currently `MockWalletProvider` — there's no real `Connection` or `AnchorProvider`. The wiring needs to work with the mock wallet too (the mock wallet has `sendTransaction`).\n5. The platform still uses mock wallet — we need to build the on-chain instruction builders but make them work through the wallet adapter interface (which currently wraps mock wallet).\n\nSince the platform is still running with a `MockWalletProvider`, I need to:\n1. Replace the mock-simulation imports in CoinflipContext with real on-chain instruction building\n2. Move `truncateAddress` and `getOppositeSide` out of mock-simulation (they're pure utils)\n3. Create instruction builder functions that build Anchor transactions\n4. Delete `mock-simulation.ts` (the coinflip one)\n5. Update imports in `ActiveMatchView.tsx` and `coinflip/index.ts`\n\nLet me check the game-engine browser export path first to make sure I know how to import from it."}],"stop_reason":nu